\f2\fs56 \cf2 Step 3 - Deploying to Heroku\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl576\sa600\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs32 \cf2 Then we'll need to create a project in heroku. Everyone will need to have a different name so\'a0
\b adjust the name so your project name is unique
\b0 .\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl460\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs28 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 \shad0 $ heroku create nomster-ken-mazaika\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl576\sa600\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \shad0 Now push it up to heroku with the following command:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl460\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs28 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 \shad0 $ git push heroku master\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl576\sa600\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \shad0 It should take a few moments to run and when it finishes it should say "Launching..." along with a URL. Copy this URL and paste it into the browser.\
To easily see our heroku url we can type:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl460\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs28 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 \shad0 $ heroku apps:info\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl576\sa600\partightenfactor0

